# LPNW Theme Development

## Theme Type

GeneratePress child theme. Keep customisations minimal and use WordPress hooks where possible rather than overriding template files.

## Brand Colours (CSS Custom Properties)

- --lpnw-navy: #1B2A4A (primary)
- --lpnw-navy-light: #2D4470
- --lpnw-amber: #E8A317 (accent/CTA)
- --lpnw-amber-light: #F5C04A
- --lpnw-white: #FFFFFF
- --lpnw-offwhite: #F7F8FA
- --lpnw-grey-light: #E5E7EB
- --lpnw-grey: #6B7280
- --lpnw-grey-dark: #374151
- --lpnw-success: #059669
- --lpnw-danger: #DC2626

## Typography

- Headings: Plus Jakarta Sans (Google Fonts), 700 weight
- Body: system font stack (-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, etc.)
- Use rem units, base 16px

## Approach

- Enqueue styles and scripts via wp_enqueue_scripts
- Use generate_ hooks for GeneratePress-specific customisations
- Keep template parts in template-parts/ directory
- Mobile-first responsive design
